i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William de Atherton II was born in 1356, in Atherton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir William de Atherton I, Knight, was 31 and his mother, Lady Jane or Joan Moberley, was 34. He married Agnes de Vernon in 1380, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1435, in his hometown, at the age of 79."},"et":{"1356–1435":"1356–1435","1347–1416":"1347–1416","1380–Female":"1380–Surnud","1384–1417":"1384–1417","1387–Male":"1387–Surnud","1370–1414":"1370–1414","1382–1435":"1382–1435","1325–1396":"1325–1396","1323–1375":"1323–1375","29 December 1414":"29. detsember 1414","1396":"1396","1384":"1384","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","circa 1375":"umbes 1375","1414":"1414","circa 1396":"umbes 1396","1435":"1435","1325":"1325","1347":"1347","1356":"1356","1323":"1323","1344":"1344","1387":"1387","1375":"1375","1417":"1417","1416":"1416","Atherton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Atherton, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Mobberley, Cheshire, England":"Mobberley, Cheshire, England","Wigan, Lancashire, England":"Wigan, Lancashire, England","Atherton, Lancashire, England":"Atherton, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1356–1435":"1356–1435","1347–1416":"1347–1416","1380–Female":"1380–Kuollut","1384–1417":"1384–1417","1387–Male":"1387–Kuollut","1370–1414":"1370–1414","1382–1435":"1382–1435","1325–1396":"1325–1396","1323–1375":"1323–1375","29 December 1414":"29. joulukuuta 1414","13